He's on the move.

253
00:23:16,041 --> 00:23:19,943
Duncan MacLeod
of the Clan MacLeod.

254
00:23:20,012 --> 00:23:22,003
Hello, Methos.

255
00:23:22,081 --> 00:23:25,175
What brings you
to my humble abode?

256
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:27,377
Need your help.

257
00:23:27,453 --> 00:23:28,750
Why me?

258
00:23:28,821 --> 00:23:31,449
(Duncan)
You're been around for 5.000 years.

259
00:23:31,523 --> 00:23:36,085
I want the benefit
of your experience.

260
00:23:36,161 --> 00:23:39,562
And I thought
it was a social call.

261
00:23:40,799 --> 00:23:42,733
You ever had nightmares?

262
00:23:42,801 --> 00:23:45,235
What kind of nightmares?

263
00:23:45,304 --> 00:23:46,498
Bloody images...

264
00:23:46,572 --> 00:23:49,405
powerful enough to even
break your meditation.

265
00:23:49,475 --> 00:23:53,343
We live violent lives, MacLeod.

266
00:23:53,412 --> 00:23:55,403
Some of that's
bound to stay with us.

267
00:23:56,448 --> 00:23:58,177
These ones came
10 years to the day...

268
00:23:58,250 --> 00:23:59,979
that Connor MacLeod disappeared.

269
00:24:01,386 --> 00:24:03,320
Connor had good reason to go.

270
00:24:03,388 --> 00:24:05,720
He told me how much
Rachel meant to him.

271
00:24:05,791 --> 00:24:09,227
There was more to it than that.
I was with him that day.

272
00:24:09,294 --> 00:24:11,194
The day Rachel was killed?

273
00:24:11,263 --> 00:24:13,595
Something wasn't right.

274
00:24:13,665 --> 00:24:14,893
