00:24:37,623 --> 00:24:39,557
Some of them come
to cherish life so much...

283
00:24:39,625 --> 00:24:43,652
that to step on an insect
or harm a blade of grass...

284
00:24:43,729 --> 00:24:45,856
becomes a violation
of their creed,

285
00:24:45,931 --> 00:24:47,694
so they place themselves
under an extreme form...

286
00:24:47,766 --> 00:24:49,791
of protective custody--

287
00:24:49,868 --> 00:24:52,530
A Sanctuary of sorts.

288
00:24:52,604 --> 00:24:54,299
Well, for an Immortal...

289
00:24:54,373 --> 00:24:56,000
who comes to abhor
the bloodshed,

290
00:24:56,074 --> 00:24:58,440
there's a similar solution--

291
00:24:58,510 --> 00:25:01,070
Away to be removed
from the game forever.

292
00:25:01,146 --> 00:25:03,171
(Methos)The price
is unimaginably high.

293
00:25:03,248 --> 00:25:05,341
but you are, for
all practical purposes,

294
00:25:05,417 --> 00:25:09,786
protected from
the violence within you.

295
00:25:09,855 --> 00:25:11,982
And it's called The Sanctuary.

296
00:25:12,057 --> 00:25:14,025
Connor would never do that.

297
00:25:14,092 --> 00:25:15,320
(Methos)Are you sure?

298
00:25:15,394 --> 00:25:17,328
It's been around since
before you were born.

299
00:25:17,396 --> 00:25:19,626
At least until last night.

300
00:25:19,698 --> 00:25:21,461
What happened last night?

301
00:25:21,533 --> 00:25:24,400
It was annihilated.

302
00:25:40,385 --> 00:25:42,785
(Connor)
Hey. Duncan, what's the matter?

303
00:25:42,855 --> 00:25:43,844
(Duncan)The British...

304
00:25:43,922 --> 00:25:45,514
destroyed the clans, Connor.

305
00:25:45,591 --> 00:25:47,354
Scotland's finished.

306
00:25:47,426 --> 00:25:50,452
(Connor)
Scotland will always be Scotland.

307
00:25:50,529 --> 00:25:52,429
and someday you'll go back.

308
00:25:52,497 --> 00:25:53,930
You can beton it.

309
00:25:53,999 --> 00:25:54,931
How much?

310
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,024
Aw, come on.

311
00:25:56,101 --> 00:25:58,934
Does everything have
to be a wager with you?

312
00:25:59,004 --> 00:26:00,528
Well,you're the one
that keep stelling me...

313
00:26:00,606 --> 00:26:02,836
our lives are nothing
but a boundless game.

314
00:26:02,908 --> 00:26:03,840
[Chuckles]

315
00:26:05,644 --> 00:26:06,770
[ Duncan ]
Good morning, gentlemen.

316
00:26:06,845 --> 00:26:09,336
What seems to be
the problem here?

317
00:26:09,414 --> 00:26:12,144
[ Man ]
They refuses to pay her toll, sir.

318
00:26:12,217 --> 00:26:13,980
(Duncan)
Really? How dare they.

319
00:26:14,052 --> 00:26:15,485
These men are rogues.

320
00:26:15,554 --> 00:26:17,852
(Faith)The semenare
liar sands coundrels, sir.

321
00:26:17,923 --> 00:26:20,824
They've done nothing but
prey upon us 3 years running,

322
00:26:20,893 --> 00:26:22,861
right at this very spot.

323
00:26:22,928 --> 00:26:25,192
And by whose authority
do you act?

324
00:26:25,264 --> 00:26:26,458
By Deed of the King.

325
00:26:28,667 --> 00:26:31,465
(Connor)
There is a little X down here.

326
00:26:31,536 --> 00:26:34,664
Does the King always
sign his name with an X?

327
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:36,207
Excuse me. Sorry. Ha ha.

328
00:26:36,275 --> 00:26:37,765
I think these gentlemen
should be paid.

329
00:26:37,843 --> 00:26:39,333
That deed is a fake.

330
00:26:39,411 --> 00:26:40,742
That's a matter of opinion.

331
00:26:40,812 --> 00:26:42,871
You, sir, are
no better than they.

332
00:26:42,948 --> 00:26:45,416
That is also a matter of opinion.

333
00:26:45,484 --> 00:26:46,508
Here you go.

334
00:26:47,953 --> 00:26:49,682
Ladies.

335
00:26:49,755 --> 00:26:51,586
It's gold!

336
00:26:51,657 --> 00:26:53,022
Why not--
It's gold.

337
00:26:53,091 --> 00:26:54,524
Firstman.Ha ha.

338
00:26:54,593 --> 00:26:56,561
Hey,wait a minute.
They took my money!

339
00:26:56,628 --> 00:26:58,027
oh, it's here.

340
00:26:58,096 --> 00:26:59,563
They took my money!

341
00:26:59,631 --> 00:27:00,893
(Man)
Let's go get 'em.

342
00:27:00,966 --> 00:27:02,456
Shall we?

343
00:27:02,534 --> 00:27:03,796
[Yelling]

344
00:27:03,869 --> 00:27:05,131
Aye.

345
00:27:06,204 --> 00:27:07,501
(Man)Aah.

346
00:27:10,842 --> 00:27:12,002
-ooh.
-ooh.

347
00:27:21,553 --> 00:27:22,884
Heh heh.

348
00:27:22,955 --> 00:27:23,887
(Connor)
Not bad.

349
00:27:23,956 --> 00:27:25,116
Uh-oh.

350
00:27:26,858 --> 00:27:27,950
Mmm.

351
00:27:29,461 --> 00:27:32,259
All right boys,time to go.
Let's go!

352
00:27:32,331 --> 00:27:33,263
Come on.

353
00:27:35,167 --> 00:27:37,067
(Duncan)
Ohh. Cuckoo.

354
00:27:37,135 --> 00:27:39,103
Oh, looks heavy, huh?

355
00:27:39,171 --> 00:27:40,900
(Duncan)Looks like
you lost your edge, lad.

356
00:27:40,973 --> 00:27:41,905
(Connor)Really heavy.

357
00:27:41,974 --> 00:27:43,498
or could he be lass?

358
00:27:43,575 --> 00:27:44,906
Could be.

359
00:27:44,977 --> 00:27:45,909
Could be.

360
00:27:45,978 --> 00:27:47,502
[Groaning]

361
00:27:49,381 --> 00:27:50,541
Hyah!

362
00:27:51,883 --> 00:27:52,815
(Drier)Come on.

363
00:27:52,884 --> 00:27:55,318
Hyah.Hyah.

364
00:27:57,589 --> 00:27:58,521
Hyah!

365
00:29:49,267 --> 00:29:51,098
(Bombs Exploding)

366
00:29:51,169 --> 00:29:53,034
(Duncan)
Corporal Duncan MacLeod, sir.

367
00:29:53,105 --> 00:29:55,665
I'e come to pick up
the wounded.

368
00:30:24,536 --> 00:30:26,470
[ Indistinct Chatter]

369
00:30:33,411 --> 00:30:34,742
You've improved greatly.

370
00:30:34,813 --> 00:30:36,337
Ah,you really think so?

371
00:30:41,753 --> 00:30:42,685
No.

372
00:30:43,822 --> 00:30:45,221
I'm Just being gracious.

373
00:30:45,290 --> 00:30:45,847
Hmm.

374
00:30:47,859 --> 00:30:49,690
Now, remember.

375
00:30:49,761 --> 00:30:51,422
You are only immortal...

376
00:30:51,496 --> 00:30:54,021
as long as you
can keep your head...

377
00:30:54,099 --> 00:30:55,259
on your shoulders.

378
00:30:58,904 --> 00:31:00,030
[ Duncan ] Gahh.

379
00:31:00,105 --> 00:31:03,734
Duncan,what you give up
to your adversary...

380
00:31:03,808 --> 00:31:05,867
in defeat...

381
00:31:05,944 --> 00:31:07,002
is everything.

382
00:31:07,078 --> 00:31:09,171
I know.
And at that point,

383
00:31:09,247 --> 00:31:11,147
I'm very,very dead.
Come on!

384
00:31:11,216 --> 00:31:12,148
Heh heh heh.

385
00:31:12,217 --> 00:31:14,685
Not Just dead, Duncan--

386
00:31:14,753 --> 00:31:15,685
Empty!

387
00:31:18,490 --> 00:31:20,583
Aye, Connor, I know.
It's called the Quickening.

388
00:31:20,659 --> 00:31:22,752
our strength and knowledge,
our life essence,

389
00:31:22,827 --> 00:31:24,454
flows into the victor,feeds him,

390
00:31:24,529 --> 00:31:26,292
and makes him stronger,yes?

391
00:31:26,364 --> 00:31:28,525
It's what drives
the other Immortals...

392
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:29,567
to kill us,

393
00:31:29,634 --> 00:31:31,124
and what forces us...

394
00:31:31,203 --> 00:31:32,795
to be smarter,
better than the rest.

395
00:31:32,871 --> 00:31:35,032
[Groans]
I understand.

396
00:31:36,641 --> 00:31:37,903
Ooh.

397
00:31:40,345 --> 00:31:41,277
You do?

398
00:31:42,547 --> 00:31:43,775
Ohh.

399
00:31:43,848 --> 00:31:44,780
(Connor)Good.

400
00:31:46,618 --> 00:31:48,483
[Groans]
I slipped.

401
00:31:48,553 --> 00:31:51,545
Listen, soon you and I
will have to part.

402
00:31:51,623 --> 00:31:54,023
There is one more thing
I want to give to you.

403
00:31:57,062 --> 00:31:57,994
[Grunts]

404
00:31:58,063 --> 00:31:58,995
Va ia. Va ia.

405
00:31:59,064 --> 00:32:00,224
Ho ho ho.

406
00:32:00,298 --> 00:32:01,492
oh, aye!

407
00:32:01,566 --> 00:32:05,024
oh, aye.This is
much more to my liking.

408
00:32:05,103 --> 00:32:06,035
Good.

409
00:32:06,104 --> 00:32:07,696
Bah! Heh heh heh.

410
00:32:07,772 --> 00:32:08,704
Heh heh heh.

411
00:32:09,774 --> 00:32:11,036
Attack me.

412
00:32:12,577 --> 00:32:14,135
But you've got your back to me.

413
00:32:15,313 --> 00:32:18,578
It's not always
about strength, Duncan.

414
00:32:18,650 --> 00:32:19,617
Attack me!

415
00:32:25,857 --> 00:32:27,188
Aah!

416
00:32:27,259 --> 00:32:30,092
It's about manipulation
of the mind...

417
00:32:33,999 --> 00:32:35,591
as well as the body.

418
00:32:35,667 --> 00:32:38,397
Aye, but now I'm in control.

419
00:32:38,470 --> 00:32:40,802
Heh heh heh,Are you?

420
00:32:44,509 --> 00:32:45,441
[Grunts]

421
00:32:47,912 --> 00:32:51,040
Remember well, my friend.

422
00:32:51,116 --> 00:32:54,608
Properly executed,
this move is unstoppable.

423
00:32:55,954 --> 00:32:59,355
Properly executed,
we'll have this talk again.

424
00:33:07,899 --> 00:33:10,993
[Wind Blows]

425
00:33:22,781 --> 00:33:24,544
Who are you?

426
00:33:24,616 --> 00:33:27,278
A friend... or a lover.

427
00:33:27,352 --> 00:33:29,377
or a wife.

428
00:33:29,454 --> 00:33:30,546
Kate?

429
00:33:30,622 --> 00:33:32,146
Attaboy.

430
00:33:32,223 --> 00:33:35,215
Except I'm Faith now.

431
00:33:35,293 --> 00:33:37,818
Part of the make over.

432
00:33:37,896 --> 00:33:39,488
Whatare you doing here?

433
00:33:40,532 --> 00:33:42,295
Remember our wedding day,
Duncan?

434
00:33:42,367 --> 00:33:43,800
I do.

435
00:33:45,103 --> 00:33:48,004
[Sighs]
The way we danced.

436
00:33:48,073 --> 00:33:49,472
[Scottish Music Playing]

437
00:33:49,541 --> 00:33:51,065
I felt like we were flying.

438
00:33:59,784 --> 00:34:02,617
of course,
we did come down...

439
00:34:02,687 --> 00:34:03,619
didn't we?

440
00:34:07,025 --> 00:34:08,617
Crashing.

441
00:34:11,696 --> 00:34:12,628
(Motorcyle Engines
Rewing)

442
00:34:12,697 --> 00:34:14,255
oh, shit.

443
00:34:22,774 --> 00:34:26,107
(Man)It's time to show
our Immortal brother...

444
00:34:26,177 --> 00:34:29,442
a thing or two.

445
00:34:38,723 --> 00:34:40,623
Somebody order
a club sandwich?

446
00:34:40,692 --> 00:34:43,126
He's funny.
Nice outfit,too.

447
00:34:43,194 --> 00:34:45,924
Faith, I told you I look
like a fuckin' orange!

448
00:34:45,997 --> 00:34:48,522
I'm not dressing you black, Bob.
Trust me.

449
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:49,498
Who are they?

450
00:34:49,567 --> 00:34:52,866
Friends.

451
00:34:52,937 --> 00:34:54,404
What, it's a team sport now?

452
00:34:54,472 --> 00:34:55,962
What,you didn't know?

453
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:59,373
It's a whole new ball game.

454
00:34:59,444 --> 00:35:01,378
Aah!

455
00:35:18,463 --> 00:35:19,987
Hey!

456
00:35:21,833 --> 00:35:23,095
Nice bat.

457
00:35:35,413 --> 00:35:36,345
Aargh!

458
00:35:36,414 --> 00:35:37,938
Told you I was gonna cut you.

459
00:35:48,092 --> 00:35:49,457
[Growls]
Aaah!

460
00:35:56,601 --> 00:35:58,569
Let my man Jin Ke
deal with him.

461
00:36:01,139 --> 00:36:03,573
Jin Ke...

462
00:36:03,641 --> 00:36:05,268
who served with
the Emperor Chin.

463
00:36:05,343 --> 00:36:07,607
The same man.

464
00:36:07,679 --> 00:36:09,704
Some people say
you're a man of honor.

465
00:36:09,781 --> 00:36:11,715
What do you know about honor?

466
00:36:13,618 --> 00:36:15,279
oh, great.

467
00:36:16,654 --> 00:36:17,814
Yaah!

468
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:04,664
Honor's not in a weapon.

469
00:37:04,736 --> 00:37:05,998
It's in the man.

470
00:37:34,098 --> 00:37:35,725
(Kell)Enough.

471
00:37:38,636 --> 00:37:41,628
Boys, boys.

472
00:37:41,706 --> 00:37:44,300
(Kell)I do apologize.

473
00:37:44,375 --> 00:37:46,900
When it comes to discipline.

474
00:37:46,978 --> 00:37:50,880
the first hundred years
are the hardest.

475
00:37:54,285 --> 00:37:55,343
Ohh!

476
00:37:56,821 --> 00:37:57,753
Ohh!

477
00:38:00,058 --> 00:38:01,923
Guess I'm not much
of a swords guy.

478
00:38:01,993 --> 00:38:06,555
I thought I told you to stop.

479
00:38:08,533 --> 00:38:09,500
(Carlos)Yeah, well.

480
00:38:09,567 --> 00:38:10,829
I stopped.

481
00:38:10,902 --> 00:38:11,926
Tell me, Carlos.

482
00:38:12,003 --> 00:38:14,471
How much is your life worth?

483
00:38:14,539 --> 00:38:17,007
Don't start this bullshit, man.

484
00:38:17,075 --> 00:38:19,805
(Kell)'Cause the only way
to win your freedom...

485
00:38:19,877 --> 00:38:21,572
is to kill me.

486
00:38:21,646 --> 00:38:22,578
You're crazy.

487
00:38:22,647 --> 00:38:23,739
Am I?

488
00:38:23,815 --> 00:38:25,806
Then go ahead.

489
00:38:25,883 --> 00:38:28,784
Stop the madness.

490
00:38:28,853 --> 00:38:30,445
[Tires Squealing]

491
00:38:30,521 --> 00:38:33,752
Can you live with the fear?

492
00:38:33,825 --> 00:38:36,623
Can you live
with the weakness?

493
00:38:39,197 --> 00:38:41,256
[Saw Buzzes]

494
00:38:41,332 --> 00:38:43,129
Weakness, Carlos.

495
00:38:47,905 --> 00:38:49,634
I call this...

496
00:38:49,707 --> 00:38:52,471
decap with a twist--

497
00:38:52,543 --> 00:38:53,771
No sugar.

498
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:39,016
[Gasping]

499
00:39:40,358 --> 00:39:41,950
Watchers?

500
00:39:42,026 --> 00:39:43,288
Huh?

501
00:39:45,663 --> 00:39:47,790
Watchers observe Immortals.

502
00:39:47,865 --> 00:39:50,060
They're no tsupposed
to interfere.

503
00:39:50,134 --> 00:39:52,830
Unfortunately, our role
has changed somewhat.

504
00:39:52,904 --> 00:39:54,269
Why?

505
00:39:54,338 --> 00:39:56,272
Because the rules
has been broken.

506
00:39:56,340 --> 00:40:00,276
one of your kind
has gone renegade.

507
00:40:03,014 --> 00:40:05,676
In doing so, he's gained
himself a sizable advantage.

508
00:40:05,750 --> 00:40:08,344
One that'll be
impossible to overcome.

509
00:40:08,419 --> 00:40:09,750
Nobody's unbeatable.

510
00:40:09,821 --> 00:40:12,346
Oh,yes, Duncan. He is.

511
00:40:16,094 --> 00:40:17,584
Unbeatable.

512
00:40:21,365 --> 00:40:22,627
No.

513
00:40:24,869 --> 00:40:26,803
[Grunting]

514
00:40:32,910 --> 00:40:33,842
Ahh.

515
00:40:33,911 --> 00:40:34,843
[Grunts]

516
00:40:34,912 --> 00:40:36,004
Sorry about that.

517
00:40:37,348 --> 00:40:40,215
There must always be
two of your kind.

518
00:40:40,284 --> 00:40:41,876
As long as there are two,

519
00:40:41,953 --> 00:40:43,545
and you're kept from fighting,

520
00:40:43,621 --> 00:40:45,486
then the prize is safe.

521
00:40:45,556 --> 00:40:48,582
The Sanctuary must not fail again.

522
00:40:48,659 --> 00:40:49,887
You're insane.

523
00:40:49,961 --> 00:40:52,395
(Duncan)
Get yourself another volunteer.

524
00:40:52,463 --> 00:40:56,422
We had a number of volunteers!

525
00:40:56,501 --> 00:40:59,902
Sadly,that's
no longer the case.

526
00:40:59,971 --> 00:41:01,495
You'll beware housed,

527
00:41:01,572 --> 00:41:02,971
hidden away.

528
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:04,268
Go to hell.

529
00:41:04,342 --> 00:41:05,536
Don't worry.

530
00:41:06,744 --> 00:41:09,406
[ Distorted ]
The drugs'll kick in momentarily.

531
00:41:14,719 --> 00:41:16,653
(Heavy Breathing)

532
00:41:22,026 --> 00:41:23,960
[Woman Screaming]

533
00:41:29,167 --> 00:41:30,259
[Gasps]

534
00:41:32,103 --> 00:41:34,298
[ Horse Neighing]

535
00:41:34,372 --> 00:41:36,306
[Swords Clanging]

536
00:41:37,842 --> 00:41:39,571
[Gasps]

537
00:41:48,753 --> 00:41:49,845
(Connor)Get up.

538
00:41:51,022 --> 00:41:52,114
Get up.

539
00:41:59,664 --> 00:42:02,633
You have better things to do
than lie there on your ass.

540
00:42:03,701 --> 00:42:05,293
Who are you?

541
00:42:05,369 --> 00:42:07,701
Someone who knows
more about you...

542
00:42:07,772 --> 00:42:09,467
than you know about yourself.

543
00:42:09,540 --> 00:42:10,837
Are you a demon?

544
00:42:10,908 --> 00:42:12,933
Heh, hehheh.

545
00:42:13,010 --> 00:42:14,341
I've been called that...

546
00:42:14,412 --> 00:42:15,538
and worse.

547
00:42:17,715 --> 00:42:19,979
I'm Connor MacLeod
of the Clan MacLeod.

548
00:42:20,051 --> 00:42:21,814
Connor MacLeod?

549
00:42:21,886 --> 00:42:24,878
And like you, my friend,

550
00:42:24,956 --> 00:42:26,981
I have a hard time dying.

551
00:42:36,234 --> 00:42:38,168
(Metal Tools Rattling)

552
00:42:43,341 --> 00:42:44,467
Dawson?

553
00:42:45,743 --> 00:42:47,267
Heh,you look like shit.

554
00:42:47,345 --> 00:42:48,471
Thanks.

555
00:42:48,546 --> 00:42:50,013
How long have I--

556
00:42:50,081 --> 00:42:50,945
We'll talk about it later.

557
00:42:51,015 --> 00:42:51,982
We gotta get outta here.

558
00:42:52,049 --> 00:42:54,984
Come on, can you walk?

559
00:42:55,052 --> 00:42:56,019
Yeah.

560
00:42:56,087 --> 00:42:57,179
Uhh.

561
00:43:13,804 --> 00:43:16,170
(Duncan)Go. Go.

562
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:17,571
What are you doing here?

563
00:43:17,642 --> 00:43:18,506
(Methos)
Keeping tabs on you.

564
00:43:18,576 --> 00:43:20,043
(Duncan)Yeah?

565
00:43:20,111 --> 00:43:21,339
Well...

566
00:43:21,412 --> 00:43:22,674
someone should keep tabs...

567
00:43:22,747 --> 00:43:24,510
on that psychotic asshole
back there.

568
00:43:24,582 --> 00:43:26,174
Didn't you get it
back in London?

569
00:43:26,250 --> 00:43:28,548
(Methos)
These guys don't play by the rules.

570
00:43:28,619 --> 00:43:30,348
You don't know what
you're up against, Mac.

571
00:43:30,421 --> 00:43:31,718
So people keep telling me.

572
00:43:31,789 --> 00:43:33,086
Stop the car.

573
00:43:33,157 --> 00:43:35,591
I managed to liberate that
from their lost and found.

574
00:43:35,660 --> 00:43:37,525
There's blood on it.

575
00:43:37,595 --> 00:43:39,460
I didn't say it was easy.

576
00:43:39,530 --> 00:43:40,462
Pull over.

577
00:43:40,531 --> 00:43:42,431
(Methos)What?

578
00:43:42,500 --> 00:43:43,990
Pull over.

579
00:43:44,068 --> 00:43:46,696
(Dawson)
MacLeod, tell me something.

580
00:43:46,771 --> 00:43:47,863
Mac, hear him out!

581
00:43:47,939 --> 00:43:50,430
Mac!Will you
tell me something?

582
00:43:50,508 --> 00:43:52,942
Now, how many Quickenings
have you had?

583
00:43:55,513 --> 00:43:57,071
How many heads
have you taken?

584
00:43:57,148 --> 00:43:59,139
I don't keep score.

585
00:43:59,784 --> 00:44:01,445
Well,we do.

586
00:44:08,859 --> 00:44:11,293
(Computer)
MacLeod, Connor.

587
00:44:11,362 --> 00:44:12,624
What's that?

588
00:44:12,697 --> 00:44:14,426
The Watchers' version
of a resume.

589
00:44:17,969 --> 00:44:20,563
(Dawson)It's a bit like
handicap ping horses. I know.

590
00:44:20,638 --> 00:44:21,969
but it's part
of the gig, all right?

591
00:44:23,874 --> 00:44:27,810
(Computer)
174 confirmed Immortal kills.

592
00:44:30,815 --> 00:44:32,544
Sound about right?

593
00:44:32,616 --> 00:44:34,675
So,what's your point?

594
00:44:34,752 --> 00:44:37,550
[Sighs] Here's the gentleman
you met in Connor's loft.

595
00:44:40,758 --> 00:44:44,888
(Computer)
661 confirmed Immortal kills.

596
00:44:48,866 --> 00:44:51,357
Welcome to your worst nightmare.

597
00:44:51,435 --> 00:44:53,733
Sanctuary wasn't shit, pal.

598
00:44:53,804 --> 00:44:56,466
This guy is way
out of your league.

599
00:45:01,112 --> 00:45:03,478
I want to see
Connor MacLeod's body.

600
00:45:03,547 --> 00:45:06,345
Why?

601
00:45:06,417 --> 00:45:07,748
[ Duncan ] Something
doesn't make sense.

602
00:45:09,053 --> 00:45:10,680
What are you saying?

603
00:45:10,755 --> 00:45:14,350
I think he's saying
he wants to see the body.

604
00:45:14,425 --> 00:45:16,188
Well, it's gonna be a rough I.D.

605
00:45:16,260 --> 00:45:18,751
They're all missing their heads!

606
00:45:30,007 --> 00:45:33,443
[ Harmonica ]

607
00:45:59,203 --> 00:46:01,535
We gave 'em
a Christian burial, MacLeod.

608
00:46:01,605 --> 00:46:02,867
It was decent,you know.

609
00:46:02,940 --> 00:46:04,601
Said all the right words.

610
00:46:04,675 --> 00:46:07,143
Can't begin to tell you
how reassuring that is.

611
00:46:07,211 --> 00:46:08,610
(Dawson)With all these
unexplained corpses.

612
00:46:08,679 --> 00:46:12,445
Well, we had to take it
off the beaten track.

613
00:46:12,516 --> 00:46:14,108
End of the road,Joe.

614
00:46:16,854 --> 00:46:17,786
Thanks.

615
00:46:19,523 --> 00:46:21,991
You watch your ass, MacLeod.

616
00:46:22,059 --> 00:46:24,323
It's not my ass
I'm worried about.

617
00:46:28,165 --> 00:46:29,757
Did I happen to mention
about all this...

618
00:46:29,834 --> 00:46:31,028
coming to a bad end?

619
00:46:31,102 --> 00:46:33,195
No, Methos.

620
00:46:33,270 --> 00:46:34,862
I don't believe you did.

621
00:46:40,945 --> 00:46:42,344
You were gonna stay and dig.

622
00:46:42,413 --> 00:46:45,075
Dig? Oh,yeah!

623
00:46:45,149 --> 00:46:46,514
(Car Door Closes)

624
00:47:03,100 --> 00:47:04,965
(Thunder)

625
00:47:09,573 --> 00:47:13,236
(Duncan)I need to know
if he's still alive, Professor.

626
00:47:13,310 --> 00:47:16,768
I want to see
Connor MacLeod's body.

627
00:47:16,847 --> 00:47:20,874
(Methos)One of your kind
has gone renegade.

628
00:47:26,056 --> 00:47:28,923
(Connor)
People change, Duncan.

629
00:47:28,993 --> 00:47:30,483
You'll learn that.

630
00:47:34,632 --> 00:47:36,930
[Wind Blows]

631
00:47:50,548 --> 00:47:52,982
[Connor Speaking
Native Language]

632
00:47:57,855 --> 00:47:59,049
No.

633
00:48:06,697 --> 00:48:08,392
What are you doing here?

634
00:48:09,934 --> 00:48:12,732
You walked out
on your life, Connor.

635
00:48:12,803 --> 00:48:13,792
Why?

636
00:48:16,874 --> 00:48:18,603
I had my reasons.

637
00:48:18,676 --> 00:48:20,303
Reasons?

638
00:48:23,214 --> 00:48:25,648
Every life I touch ends...

639
00:48:26,850 --> 00:48:27,817
brutally...

640
00:48:28,953 --> 00:48:30,318
and for no reason.

641
00:48:30,387 --> 00:48:31,979
It's a curse...

642
00:48:32,056 --> 00:48:34,354
that's followed me for centuries.

643
00:48:34,425 --> 00:48:35,722
[ Laughs]

644
00:48:35,793 --> 00:48:40,253
I can't outrun it,
and I can't outlive it.

645
00:48:42,266 --> 00:48:44,291
Rachel's death made you
the last soul on this planet...

646
00:48:44,368 --> 00:48:45,665
that means a damn to me.

647
00:48:45,736 --> 00:48:48,569
I thought there was a way out.

648
00:48:48,639 --> 00:48:49,663
The Sanctuary?

649
00:48:51,575 --> 00:48:52,507
Yes.

650
00:48:55,246 --> 00:48:56,736
The Sanctuary.

651
00:48:58,048 --> 00:48:59,174
So, how did you escape?

652
00:49:00,851 --> 00:49:02,478
I didn't escape.

653
00:49:04,622 --> 00:49:05,748
I was let go.

654
00:49:09,193 --> 00:49:12,424
I couldn't see the slaughter,

655
00:49:12,496 --> 00:49:13,588
only heard it...

656
00:49:15,032 --> 00:49:15,964
and felt it.

657
00:49:18,302 --> 00:49:20,031
[Wind Blows]

658
00:49:43,494 --> 00:49:45,428
[ People Yell ]

659
00:49:48,699 --> 00:49:50,064
Jacob Kell.

660
00:50:01,512 --> 00:50:03,173
So, here we are--

661
00:50:03,247 --> 00:50:05,442
Both immortal.

662
00:50:05,516 --> 00:50:07,848
(Kell)
Missed the signs,

663
00:50:07,918 --> 00:50:09,886
didn't we?

664
00:50:09,953 --> 00:50:13,548
But we were both
so new at the game.

665
00:50:13,624 --> 00:50:15,558
[Thunder]

666
00:50:16,627 --> 00:50:17,958
[ Duncan ]
Connor.

667
00:50:19,296 --> 00:50:22,493
What a glorious sight.

668
00:50:24,301 --> 00:50:26,428
Just look, Connor.

669
00:50:28,272 --> 00:50:31,764
Look back at the endless
travesties of your life,

670
00:50:31,842 --> 00:50:33,400
and you'll see me,

671
00:50:33,477 --> 00:50:36,173
always there
waiting in the shadows.

672
00:50:36,246 --> 00:50:38,043
When friends and loers...

673
00:50:38,115 --> 00:50:39,742
are wiped from your sight-

674
00:50:40,851 --> 00:50:41,875
I'm there.

675
00:50:41,952 --> 00:50:43,681
When those you cherish...

676
00:50:43,754 --> 00:50:46,814
die abruptly and for no reason-

677
00:50:46,890 --> 00:50:48,824
I'm there for you.

678
00:50:49,927 --> 00:50:51,326
And when your cellmates...

679
00:50:51,395 --> 00:50:54,125
in their so-called Sanctuary...

680
00:50:54,198 --> 00:50:57,258
are left twitching
like headless chickens-

681
00:50:58,902 --> 00:50:59,834
Guess who?

682
00:51:05,075 --> 00:51:06,042
(Duncan)Connor.

683
00:51:06,110 --> 00:51:08,442
(Connor)
Stay out of it, Duncan.

684
00:51:12,883 --> 00:51:15,283
Would you kill
an unarmed man...

685
00:51:15,352 --> 00:51:16,546
again, Connor?

686
00:51:17,855 --> 00:51:18,787
(Kell)Oh.

687
00:51:18,856 --> 00:51:21,552
You didn't know, Duncan?

688
00:51:22,793 --> 00:51:25,660
Because you didn't tell him.

689
00:51:25,729 --> 00:51:27,924
Would that finally
put the agony...

690
00:51:27,998 --> 00:51:30,262
in your soul to rest?

691
00:51:30,334 --> 00:51:33,235
Then go ahead.

692
00:51:33,303 --> 00:51:35,931
Send me home.

693
00:51:37,508 --> 00:51:38,566
What's stopping you?

694
00:51:38,642 --> 00:51:39,973
Honor?

695
00:51:41,044 --> 00:51:42,841
Guilt?

696
00:51:42,913 --> 00:51:45,177
The nagging sense that maybe you,

697
00:51:45,249 --> 00:51:46,580
more than I, deserve to die?

698
00:51:46,650 --> 00:51:48,049
(Thunder)

699
00:51:48,118 --> 00:51:49,745
Or somewhere along the way...

700
00:51:49,820 --> 00:51:53,517
did you Just lose your nerve?

701
00:51:53,590 --> 00:51:54,887
It's holyground, Connor.

702
00:51:54,958 --> 00:51:56,892
Ooh.

703
00:51:56,960 --> 00:51:58,552
Yes.

704
00:51:58,629 --> 00:52:01,257
Take your shot.

705
00:52:02,433 --> 00:52:04,060
What better chance than now?

706
00:52:04,134 --> 00:52:06,261
Do it.

707
00:52:06,336 --> 00:52:11,239
Do it for your sweet mother.

708
00:52:11,308 --> 00:52:13,606
Aah!

709
00:52:13,677 --> 00:52:16,544
or the sweet little war orphan...

710
00:52:16,613 --> 00:52:20,515
Rachel Ellenstein...

711
00:52:23,754 --> 00:52:25,016
who, if I'm not mistaken,

712
00:52:25,088 --> 00:52:27,682
you raised
as your own daughter.

713
00:52:27,758 --> 00:52:29,919
Tell me, do they even begin...

714
00:52:29,993 --> 00:52:32,393
to equal for the murder
of a man of God...

715
00:52:32,463 --> 00:52:34,624
who raised me as his own son?

716
00:52:34,698 --> 00:52:36,996
Aah!

717
00:52:38,769 --> 00:52:40,202
Slow...

718
00:52:40,270 --> 00:52:41,999
close--

719
00:52:43,073 --> 00:52:45,098
Feels good, doesn't it?

720
00:52:45,175 --> 00:52:47,302
But look at you.

721
00:52:48,412 --> 00:52:51,381
Even now,you're afraid--

722
00:52:51,448 --> 00:52:53,211
Afraid you'll lose.

723
00:52:53,283 --> 00:52:55,308
That's your true fear, isn't it?

724
00:52:55,385 --> 00:52:57,979
The thought of giving up
your essence to me,

725
00:52:58,055 --> 00:53:01,786
making me
even stronger by it.

726
00:53:03,594 --> 00:53:05,391
What's wrong?

727
00:53:05,462 --> 00:53:09,091
Don't you want
to be inside me?

728
00:53:35,225 --> 00:53:38,217
I want you to think back
to this moment, Connor!

729
00:53:44,668 --> 00:53:46,727
In the endless nights ahead!

730
00:53:46,803 --> 00:53:48,361
(Connor)Aah.

731
00:54:02,185 --> 00:54:03,379
And know...

732
00:54:03,453 --> 00:54:04,852
Aah!

733
00:54:04,922 --> 00:54:06,890
every time
you close your eyes...

734
00:54:06,957 --> 00:54:10,449
from now to eternity,
I'll bet here!

735
00:54:13,063 --> 00:54:16,692
Ripping apart the ones
you care about most!

736
00:54:16,767 --> 00:54:18,257
Aah!

737
00:54:26,810 --> 00:54:30,644
It's never over,
Connor MacLeod.

738
00:54:30,714 --> 00:54:33,478
Living is what matters.

739
00:54:33,550 --> 00:54:36,678
And you will live with this.

740
00:54:36,753 --> 00:54:37,720
Count on it.

741
00:54:37,788 --> 00:54:39,551
one far-off day,

742
00:54:39,623 --> 00:54:42,091
you and I will be
the only two remaining.

743
00:54:42,159 --> 00:54:43,592
You will look back on this...

744
00:54:43,660 --> 00:54:47,619
and know you had
one chance to stop me.

745
00:54:47,698 --> 00:54:49,165
You failed.

746
00:54:49,232 --> 00:54:51,132
But until thatday,

747
00:54:51,201 --> 00:54:53,226
I will take my vengeance...

748
00:54:53,303 --> 00:54:55,328
on those you love.

749
00:54:55,405 --> 00:54:59,603
Your ling...
has been my prize.

750
00:55:00,677 --> 00:55:01,939
For old times' sake.

751
00:55:03,747 --> 00:55:05,738
(Jacob)He is your son.

752
00:55:08,251 --> 00:55:13,018
You, on the other hand...

753
00:55:15,225 --> 00:55:18,922
are on borrowed time.

754
00:55:18,996 --> 00:55:20,190
Call you.

755
00:55:25,002 --> 00:55:26,867
Is what he said true?

756
00:55:31,341 --> 00:55:32,308
Is it?

757
00:55:32,376 --> 00:55:34,003
Believe only what your heart...

758
00:55:34,077 --> 00:55:36,272
and conscience tell you.

759
00:55:38,548 --> 00:55:40,209
Connor...

760
00:55:40,283 --> 00:55:42,376
with time, anything
can be forgiven.

761
00:55:42,452 --> 00:55:44,215
You taught me that.

762
00:55:49,593 --> 00:55:51,322
Did I?

763
00:56:06,476 --> 00:56:08,671
[Clapping, Laughing,
Music Playing]

764
00:56:20,190 --> 00:56:22,215
Oh, look at Dave. Dave!

765
00:56:22,292 --> 00:56:23,759
(Kate)Behave yourself, Duncan.

766
00:56:23,827 --> 00:56:25,692
(Man)No more talking.

767
00:56:25,762 --> 00:56:29,664
May all your hardships fade away.

768
00:56:29,733 --> 00:56:32,031
(Man)
Till night becomes morn.

769
00:56:32,102 --> 00:56:35,071
let loe remain
to guide your way.

770
00:56:35,138 --> 00:56:37,197
Till the day we are reborn.

771
00:56:38,442 --> 00:56:40,342
Till the day we are reborn.

772
00:56:40,410 --> 00:56:41,741
Kiss her,won't you?

773
00:56:41,812 --> 00:56:44,246
[CheeringAnd Clapping]

774
00:56:50,620 --> 00:56:51,848
(Duncan)Connor?

775
00:56:53,557 --> 00:56:56,924
(Duncan. Laughing)
I thought you'd never get here.

776
00:56:56,993 --> 00:56:59,154
Connor!

777
00:57:02,332 --> 00:57:05,597
(Connor)You know
Kate is like us, immortal.

778
00:57:05,669 --> 00:57:07,933
Aye, I sensed something
the day we met.

779
00:57:08,004 --> 00:57:09,528
but I wasn't sure.

780
00:57:09,606 --> 00:57:12,598
Well, now you know.

781
00:57:12,676 --> 00:57:15,167
And you know as well as I do...

782
00:57:15,245 --> 00:57:19,045
that her Immortality
can only be triggered...

783
00:57:19,116 --> 00:57:22,381
by the shock of a violent death.

784
00:57:22,452 --> 00:57:24,511
Yes, I do.

785
00:57:24,588 --> 00:57:25,577
And without such a death,

786
00:57:25,655 --> 00:57:27,054
she will simply
grow old and die.

787
00:57:27,124 --> 00:57:28,785
Yes, I know, Connor.

788
00:57:28,859 --> 00:57:31,419
Is that what you came
to tell me on my wedding day?

789
00:57:31,495 --> 00:57:33,986
Come on.
Drink up, man.

790
00:57:35,532 --> 00:57:37,693
[Sets Down Mug]
No.

791
00:57:37,768 --> 00:57:40,066
I was wondering.

792
00:57:41,571 --> 00:57:43,539
Does she know?

793
00:57:45,776 --> 00:57:46,708
Why?

794
00:57:51,481 --> 00:57:55,144
Many years
after I was married,

795
00:57:57,521 --> 00:57:59,455
one night...

796
00:57:59,523 --> 00:58:01,991
I found Heather
in front of the house.

797
00:58:02,058 --> 00:58:05,516
She had a knife in one hand...

798
00:58:05,595 --> 00:58:07,495
and her hair in the other.

799
00:58:07,564 --> 00:58:08,690
When I asked her...

800
00:58:08,765 --> 00:58:11,097
why she had done such
a thing to herself.

801
00:58:11,168 --> 00:58:13,659
she said it was
the one part of her...

802
00:58:13,737 --> 00:58:15,932
that would never age.

803
00:58:16,006 --> 00:58:18,440
It would forever
remain the same...

804
00:58:18,508 --> 00:58:21,033
as when I first
fell in love with her.

805
00:58:22,179 --> 00:58:24,909
That's how she wanted me
to remember her.

806
00:58:24,981 --> 00:58:27,745
Why are you telling me this?

807
00:58:27,818 --> 00:58:30,685
Because I once loved a woman...

808
00:58:30,754 --> 00:58:32,119
more than life itself--

809
00:58:35,892 --> 00:58:37,883
and I watched her die.

810
00:58:37,961 --> 00:58:43,297
Unlike me,you have a choice.

811
00:58:59,149 --> 00:59:01,447
What would you have me tell her?

812
00:59:01,518 --> 00:59:03,816
I'd tell her nothing.

813
00:59:03,887 --> 00:59:04,945
She wouldn't believe you anyway.

814
00:59:05,021 --> 00:59:06,511
Then I can do nothing.

815
00:59:06,590 --> 00:59:08,922
She's in the flower of her youth.

816
00:59:08,992 --> 00:59:11,790
Enjoy the moment,
and let it pass.

817
00:59:11,862 --> 00:59:14,160
And if it were you in my place?

818
00:59:14,231 --> 00:59:16,256
I was in your place!

819
00:59:18,201 --> 00:59:20,795
But I thank God
I never had the choice.

820
00:59:20,871 --> 00:59:22,668
I love Kate,

821
00:59:22,739 --> 00:59:24,866
and I will hold on to her
as long as I can.

822
00:59:24,941 --> 00:59:27,466
And that is all I can do!

823
00:59:32,649 --> 00:59:34,583
[ Duncan ]
Forever, my love.

824
00:59:36,620 --> 00:59:38,315
Until the day we are reborn.

825
00:59:40,023 --> 00:59:41,320
Until the day we are reborn.

826
01:00:27,203 --> 01:00:29,137
[Wind Blows]

827
01:00:37,914 --> 01:00:39,848
You haven't lost your touch.

828
01:00:39,916 --> 01:00:41,247
What do you want?

829
01:00:41,318 --> 01:00:42,250
To talk.

830
01:00:42,319 --> 01:00:43,411
Oh,that's a first.

831
01:00:43,486 --> 01:00:44,680
I've tried to talk to you
a thousand times--

832
01:00:44,754 --> 01:00:46,619
Get to the point.

833
01:00:46,690 --> 01:00:47,884
I was wrong.

834
01:00:47,958 --> 01:00:49,323
(Faith)Oh. no. no.

835
01:00:49,392 --> 01:00:50,916
Stealing's wrong.

836
01:00:50,994 --> 01:00:53,121
Lying's wrong.
Killing's wrong.

837
01:00:53,196 --> 01:00:55,130
What you did
goes well beyond wrong.

838
01:00:55,198 --> 01:00:56,597
Fine.

839
01:00:56,666 --> 01:00:58,463
I deserve that,

840
01:00:58,535 --> 01:00:59,968
but I want a chance
to make it right.

841
01:01:00,036 --> 01:01:01,970
You want to make it right?

842
01:01:02,038 --> 01:01:03,096
Then give me back the ability...

843
01:01:03,173 --> 01:01:04,970
to have children,

844
01:01:05,041 --> 01:01:07,441
to grow old
with the man I love.

845
01:01:07,510 --> 01:01:09,740
How about anything that
resembles a normal life?

846
01:01:09,813 --> 01:01:12,077
And you took it all
away from me.

847
01:01:12,148 --> 01:01:13,274
Those things I can't give you.

848
01:01:13,350 --> 01:01:16,410
Oh, something else
you forgot to tell me.

849
01:01:17,854 --> 01:01:18,912
Good-bye, Duncan.

850
01:01:18,989 --> 01:01:20,650
Kell can't give you
those things, either,

851
01:01:20,724 --> 01:01:24,524
so tell me, Kate,why him?

852
01:01:24,594 --> 01:01:26,152
Because I've never
known anybody...

853
01:01:26,229 --> 01:01:28,925
with such a capacity for hate--

854
01:01:28,999 --> 01:01:30,296
Except me.

855
01:01:30,367 --> 01:01:33,598
That's what's kept you
going all these years?

856
01:01:33,670 --> 01:01:34,637
Hmm?

857
01:01:37,207 --> 01:01:38,196
Fine.

858
01:01:40,677 --> 01:01:41,735
Go home, Faith.

859
01:01:43,546 --> 01:01:46,014
Take care of what's important.

860
01:02:17,781 --> 01:02:20,409
(Wind Blows)

861
01:02:51,915 --> 01:02:54,782
(Thunder clap)

862
01:03:08,331 --> 01:03:11,823
You were with him.

863
01:03:13,636 --> 01:03:16,002
A woman is a temple...

864
01:03:16,072 --> 01:03:19,701
built on a sewer.

865
01:03:19,776 --> 01:03:21,869
(Thunder Rumbling)

866
01:03:21,945 --> 01:03:25,506
Remember what you were
when I first found you.

867
01:03:27,183 --> 01:03:29,674
A whore.

868
01:03:30,954 --> 01:03:33,855
Now, look at you.

869
01:03:33,923 --> 01:03:36,289
A liberated whore.

870
01:03:36,359 --> 01:03:37,553
Fuck you.

871
01:03:37,627 --> 01:03:41,256
Oh,we'll get to that, blossom.

872
01:03:41,331 --> 01:03:43,390
But in the interim, be grateful...

873
01:03:43,466 --> 01:03:47,095
I don't take
your pretty little face off.

874
01:03:47,170 --> 01:03:50,333
Hurts, doesn't it...

875
01:03:51,774 --> 01:03:55,471
that there is something
you actually can't have?

876
01:03:56,813 --> 01:03:59,748
Hmm. I can hae...

877
01:03:59,816 --> 01:04:02,284
anything I want.

878
01:04:03,820 --> 01:04:05,788
Except me.

879
01:04:05,855 --> 01:04:08,881
[Sighs]

880
01:04:08,958 --> 01:04:12,018
I've already had you.

881
01:04:14,264 --> 01:04:16,960
(Thunder Crashing)

882
01:04:17,033 --> 01:04:18,796
[Softly]
Not really.

883
01:04:23,039 --> 01:04:26,805
Close enough.

884
01:04:26,876 --> 01:04:30,073
(Thunder)

885
01:04:49,832 --> 01:04:54,895
(Door Opening)

886
01:05:11,921 --> 01:05:15,220
(Woman Vocalizing)

887
01:05:35,278 --> 01:05:39,612
(Vocalizing Continues)

888
01:06:42,812 --> 01:06:44,006
Forever.

889
01:07:18,147 --> 01:07:20,138
(Thunder Rumbling)

890
01:07:20,216 --> 01:07:23,083
May love remain
to guide our way...

891
01:07:23,152 --> 01:07:24,983
till the day we are reborn.

892
01:07:30,193 --> 01:07:31,820
Forgive me.

893
01:07:33,496 --> 01:07:35,123
- Uhh!
- [Screams]

894
01:07:49,178 --> 01:07:51,738
I'm sorry.

895
01:07:53,449 --> 01:07:56,247
You had no right.

896
01:08:13,436 --> 01:08:15,028
-(Wind Blows)
- Uhh!

897
01:08:15,104 --> 01:08:17,038
[Thunder]

898
01:08:18,107 --> 01:08:19,802
(Duncan)Kate?

899
01:08:19,876 --> 01:08:21,366
No. Don't be frightened.

900
01:08:21,444 --> 01:08:22,638
You're immortal.
We both are.

901
01:08:22,712 --> 01:08:24,737
Aah!

902
01:08:24,814 --> 01:08:25,746
(Faith)Uhh.

903
01:08:27,383 --> 01:08:30,409
I did it for you--

904
01:08:30,486 --> 01:08:31,475
For us.

905
01:08:31,554 --> 01:08:33,021
- Uhh!
-(Duncan)Kate.

906
01:08:33,089 --> 01:08:34,021
Kate?

907
01:08:34,090 --> 01:08:35,216
oh, no!

908
01:08:35,291 --> 01:08:36,451
(Duncan)Oh. no.

909
01:08:36,526 --> 01:08:37,993
Oh. my God.
What have I done?

910
01:08:38,060 --> 01:08:39,652
Kate!

911
01:08:39,729 --> 01:08:42,027
(Faith)
You wanted this.

912
01:08:42,098 --> 01:08:45,295
You forced it on me.

913
01:08:45,368 --> 01:08:47,495
I never asked for eternity.

914
01:08:47,570 --> 01:08:49,060
[Crying]

915
01:08:49,138 --> 01:08:52,107
(Duncan)
I never wanted us to be apart.

916
01:08:56,212 --> 01:08:57,543
Would you have really understood?

917
01:08:57,613 --> 01:08:58,944
(Faith)
Which part?

918
01:08:59,015 --> 01:09:02,507
The endless, numbing
sameness of it all?

919
01:09:02,585 --> 01:09:04,883
Or never bothering
to love someone...

920
01:09:04,954 --> 01:09:08,185
because whole lifetimes
tick by so fast...

921
01:09:08,257 --> 01:09:09,519
they don't even count anymore?

922
01:09:10,827 --> 01:09:12,294
(Opens Door)

923
01:09:12,361 --> 01:09:13,692
Then why did you come?

924
01:09:15,131 --> 01:09:18,589
To see if I could feel again--

925
01:09:18,668 --> 01:09:20,499
Anything.

926
01:09:20,570 --> 01:09:22,504
(Door Closes)

927
01:09:32,849 --> 01:09:34,783
[ Elevator Bell Dings]

928
01:09:38,855 --> 01:09:40,948
You're missing the point, Kate.

929
01:09:41,023 --> 01:09:43,355
The difference
between Connor and I...

930
01:09:43,426 --> 01:09:44,825
is that as long
as you're still alive,

931
01:09:44,894 --> 01:09:46,794
there's a chance that one day...

932
01:09:46,863 --> 01:09:47,830
I might be forgiven.

933
01:09:47,897 --> 01:09:49,888
It may take years--

934
01:09:51,100 --> 01:09:52,567
Centuries, even.

935
01:09:54,003 --> 01:09:56,096
But at least I can
carry that hope inside me.

936
01:09:56,172 --> 01:09:58,732
That's one blessing
of immortality--

937
01:10:00,743 --> 01:10:02,734
There's always tomorrow.

938
01:10:05,248 --> 01:10:06,408
Even for us.

939
01:10:13,055 --> 01:10:14,989
(Bell Tolling)

940
01:10:24,901 --> 01:10:28,132
What are you doing,Jin?

941
01:10:28,204 --> 01:10:29,694
Just thinking.

942
01:10:31,307 --> 01:10:32,934
(Jin)
Men, for the most part.

943
01:10:33,009 --> 01:10:34,476
can mend their ways...

944
01:10:34,544 --> 01:10:37,377
only after they have made
a mistake.

945
01:10:39,582 --> 01:10:40,640
(Jin)One day soon.

946
01:10:40,716 --> 01:10:42,707
we will all...

947
01:10:42,785 --> 01:10:45,253
serv every little purpose to Kell,

948
01:10:45,321 --> 01:10:46,982
except dead.

949
01:11:02,805 --> 01:11:04,102
(Kell)A toast.

950
01:11:06,309 --> 01:11:08,209
I see tonight...

951
01:11:09,345 --> 01:11:12,280
as a celebration of the spirit.

952
01:11:13,883 --> 01:11:15,714
To all of you...

953
01:11:15,785 --> 01:11:17,685
who continue to stand by me--

954
01:11:17,753 --> 01:11:20,119
even those who might waver...

955
01:11:20,189 --> 01:11:21,986
at times-

956
01:11:23,326 --> 01:11:26,784
You are my flock.

957
01:11:28,130 --> 01:11:29,097
You...

958
01:11:29,165 --> 01:11:31,633
nourish my soul.

959
01:11:34,870 --> 01:11:37,202
You are all a part...

960
01:11:37,273 --> 01:11:39,537
of a great Journey--

961
01:11:39,609 --> 01:11:42,510
a 400-year quest--

962
01:11:44,480 --> 01:11:45,913
for Justice.

963
01:11:48,351 --> 01:11:51,912
(Kell)
And here, my friends.

964
01:11:51,988 --> 01:11:55,082
is the instrument
of that Justice--

965
01:11:56,859 --> 01:11:58,156
The giver...

966
01:11:58,227 --> 01:12:00,718
and taker of creation...

967
01:12:02,898 --> 01:12:05,731
baptized in blood.

968
01:12:08,871 --> 01:12:09,803
It is the living...

969
01:12:09,872 --> 01:12:12,170
that matters...

970
01:12:12,241 --> 01:12:13,674
after all.

971
01:12:18,481 --> 01:12:20,676
It sings like an angel.

972
01:12:22,151 --> 01:12:23,846
Just listen.

973
01:12:26,555 --> 01:12:28,182
(Faith Gasps)

974
01:12:32,928 --> 01:12:34,361
(Jin)Uhh.

975
01:12:40,569 --> 01:12:41,501
(Man)Uhh.

976
01:12:49,578 --> 01:12:51,136
(Carlos)Uhh.

977
01:12:51,213 --> 01:12:52,612
[Gasps]

978
01:13:04,560 --> 01:13:06,357
Till the day we are reborn.

979
01:13:08,197 --> 01:13:09,255
(Faith Gasps)

980
01:13:17,606 --> 01:13:18,868
Ohh!

981
01:13:26,716 --> 01:13:29,344
Ohh!

982
01:13:29,418 --> 01:13:33,752
Aah!

983
01:13:33,823 --> 01:13:35,814
Uhh!

984
01:13:47,737 --> 01:13:49,671
[Wind Blows]

985
01:13:55,945 --> 01:13:57,879
[ Distant Siren ]

986
01:14:03,419 --> 01:14:04,716
Kell.

987
01:14:06,055 --> 01:14:07,420
Jacob Kell.

988
01:14:16,132 --> 01:14:17,121
Connor?

989
01:14:27,576 --> 01:14:30,136
[Sighs]

990
01:14:30,212 --> 01:14:33,511
We've lived many lives,
you and I.

991
01:14:33,582 --> 01:14:35,209
We've seen things...

992
01:14:35,284 --> 01:14:38,811
that most people
could never understand.

993
01:14:38,888 --> 01:14:41,914
But now what do you see?

994
01:14:41,991 --> 01:14:44,755
I see someone who would
never kill an unarmed man.

995
01:14:46,262 --> 01:14:50,699
I also see someone
who has lost hope.

996
01:14:50,766 --> 01:14:53,200
Life brings hope and pain...

997
01:14:55,638 --> 01:14:58,607
but revenge
never brings redemption.

998
01:14:58,674 --> 01:15:01,609
The path and choice are ours.

999
01:15:08,884 --> 01:15:10,374
Connor,what the hell's going on?

1000
01:15:10,452 --> 01:15:13,353
I have chosen mine.

1001
01:15:13,422 --> 01:15:14,354
Aah!

1002
01:15:14,423 --> 01:15:15,549
What are you doing?

1003
01:15:15,624 --> 01:15:16,818
Kell's too strong,

1004
01:15:16,892 --> 01:15:19,224
and he's getting stronger.

1005
01:15:19,295 --> 01:15:21,354
Neither one of us can beat him alone.

1006
01:15:22,965 --> 01:15:24,432
Are you out of your mind?

1007
01:15:25,801 --> 01:15:27,962
Aah! If we let him win,

1008
01:15:28,037 --> 01:15:29,470
it could mean the end.

1009
01:15:35,377 --> 01:15:37,072
Connor, no!

1010
01:15:38,781 --> 01:15:41,807
Kell is going
to kill you, Duncan,

1011
01:15:41,884 --> 01:15:43,749
just to torment me,

1012
01:15:43,819 --> 01:15:45,548
and there is nothing
you can do about it--

1013
01:15:45,621 --> 01:15:46,747
Nothing.

1014
01:15:46,822 --> 01:15:48,221
I don't believe that, Connor.
Neither should you.

1015
01:15:48,290 --> 01:15:51,259
Alone, neither one of us
can beat him.

1016
01:15:51,327 --> 01:15:52,351
Together,we can.

1017
01:15:52,428 --> 01:15:54,862
You know the rules.

1018
01:15:54,930 --> 01:15:56,830
only one Immortal
can challenge another.

1019
01:15:58,133 --> 01:16:00,192
And only one will.

1020
01:16:00,269 --> 01:16:01,395
This isn't the answer.

1021
01:16:01,470 --> 01:16:03,836
Listen to me.

1022
01:16:03,906 --> 01:16:04,930
In the end,

1023
01:16:05,007 --> 01:16:07,100
there can be only one,

1024
01:16:07,176 --> 01:16:08,734
and that hasto be you.

1025
01:16:11,847 --> 01:16:12,814
No.

1026
01:16:14,183 --> 01:16:15,343
We can beat him together.

1027
01:16:15,417 --> 01:16:17,908
Then we are in agreement.

1028
01:16:28,964 --> 01:16:29,896
Enough, Connor!

1029
01:16:31,200 --> 01:16:32,224
I won't fight you.

1030
01:16:32,301 --> 01:16:35,270
I will never fight you, Connor.

1031
01:16:35,337 --> 01:16:37,305
Then you die!

1032
01:16:49,351 --> 01:16:50,283
Uhh.

1033
01:17:04,233 --> 01:17:07,669
No!You're not
doing this, Connor.

1034
01:17:07,736 --> 01:17:10,170
Oh,yes,we're doing this.

1035
01:17:10,239 --> 01:17:11,570
Every day,

1036
01:17:11,640 --> 01:17:15,371
every breath we took
was for this end.

1037
01:17:18,814 --> 01:17:22,215
Look inside
and tell me I'm wrong.

1038
01:17:42,104 --> 01:17:43,696
Aah!

1039
01:17:45,607 --> 01:17:47,905
Aah!Aah!

1040
01:17:53,282 --> 01:17:54,749
Do it!

1041
01:17:58,454 --> 01:17:59,921
I can't.

1042
01:18:03,258 --> 01:18:05,556
Remember how
you first found me?

1043
01:18:05,627 --> 01:18:07,686
Sitting in that bloody bog,

1044
01:18:07,763 --> 01:18:10,061
scared out of my mind?

1045
01:18:10,132 --> 01:18:11,963
You taught me
how to live, Connor.

1046
01:18:12,034 --> 01:18:13,262
You taught me why we live.

1047
01:18:14,503 --> 01:18:17,438
Have you forgotten all of that?

1048
01:18:18,874 --> 01:18:19,806
No.

1049
01:18:22,211 --> 01:18:24,008
our bonds...

1050
01:18:24,079 --> 01:18:28,345
are all that hold us
in this world.

1051
01:18:28,417 --> 01:18:30,351
Don't break this one.

1052
01:18:34,757 --> 01:18:36,520
Please, Connor.

1053
01:18:36,592 --> 01:18:38,025
I'm begging you.

1054
01:18:42,664 --> 01:18:44,097
It's too late.

1055
01:18:51,540 --> 01:18:54,008
This has to be done.

1056
01:18:54,076 --> 01:18:55,407
Haah!

1057
01:18:58,680 --> 01:18:59,806
No, Connor!
Not like this!

1058
01:18:59,882 --> 01:19:01,315
Come on, stop!

1059
01:19:01,383 --> 01:19:03,248
Connor, stop!

1060
01:19:03,318 --> 01:19:04,182
Duncan!

1061
01:19:08,557 --> 01:19:11,253
one of us has to die now,
old friend.

1062
01:19:13,328 --> 01:19:14,260
No.

1063
01:19:17,199 --> 01:19:18,928
And you know it.

1064
01:19:21,070 --> 01:19:22,037
No.

1065
01:19:25,874 --> 01:19:27,307
Good-bye, Duncan,

1066
01:19:28,944 --> 01:19:30,411
my true brother.

1067
01:19:33,749 --> 01:19:36,013
I love you, Connor.

1068
01:19:45,194 --> 01:19:46,252
Aah!

1069
01:19:48,964 --> 01:19:51,091
No!

1070
01:19:58,140 --> 01:20:02,702
(Connor)Aah.

1071
01:20:16,258 --> 01:20:20,160
[ No Audible Dialogue]

1072
01:20:39,615 --> 01:20:41,549
[Thunder]

1073
01:20:49,525 --> 01:20:51,459
[Screaming]

1074
01:21:05,807 --> 01:21:07,331
[Thunder]

1075
01:22:16,211 --> 01:22:18,270
(Hands Clapping)

1076
01:22:27,222 --> 01:22:28,280
Duncan.

1077
01:22:29,524 --> 01:22:31,321
Well done.

1078
01:22:35,831 --> 01:22:38,891
I ever thought
you had him in you.

1079
01:22:40,802 --> 01:22:44,568
What does it feel like
to kill a brother?

1080
01:22:45,641 --> 01:22:47,404
Feels good,

1081
01:22:47,476 --> 01:22:49,774
doesn't it?

1082
01:22:49,845 --> 01:22:52,609
You'll never know,will you?

1083
01:22:54,816 --> 01:22:58,252
Now you'll never have
Connor MacLeod's head.

1084
01:22:59,521 --> 01:23:02,513
Are you going to run?

1085
01:23:02,591 --> 01:23:05,321
Are you going to hide?

1086
01:23:08,130 --> 01:23:09,495
Run?

1087
01:23:09,564 --> 01:23:10,553
Uhh!

1088
01:23:10,632 --> 01:23:11,997
Aah!

1089
01:23:12,067 --> 01:23:14,399
(Duncan)
Brother, come on.

1090
01:23:14,469 --> 01:23:16,699
Aah!

1091
01:23:16,772 --> 01:23:18,171
[Grunts]

1092
01:23:18,240 --> 01:23:20,572
Aah!

1093
01:23:24,212 --> 01:23:27,511
-Aah!
-Aah!

1094
01:23:52,941 --> 01:23:54,875
How bad do you
want it, Duncan?

1095
01:23:57,779 --> 01:23:59,269
You'll pay!

1096
01:24:24,306 --> 01:24:25,330
Ahh!

1097
01:24:44,292 --> 01:24:47,693
ohh!

1098
01:24:57,406 --> 01:24:58,873
Duncan!

1099
01:26:19,354 --> 01:26:21,288
[Grunts]

1100
01:26:21,356 --> 01:26:24,621
Okay, Kell. Come on.
Let's do this.

1101
01:26:30,966 --> 01:26:32,490
[Camera Winding]

1102
01:26:36,137 --> 01:26:38,230
Just watch.

1103
01:27:01,530 --> 01:27:04,363
Merry Christmas.

1104
01:27:25,754 --> 01:27:27,722
A valiant effort, Duncan.

1105
01:27:28,823 --> 01:27:30,688
Too bad.

1106
01:27:30,759 --> 01:27:33,284
And this is
just the beginning.

1107
01:27:33,361 --> 01:27:35,989
You see,when
you absorbed Connor's spirit,

1108
01:27:36,064 --> 01:27:38,965
you inherited his curse.

1109
01:27:39,034 --> 01:27:40,160
Revenge...

1110
01:27:40,235 --> 01:27:41,793
is so sweet.

1111
01:27:41,870 --> 01:27:44,600
I wonder who we'll start with?

1112
01:27:51,246 --> 01:27:52,178
Oh, Kate.

1113
01:27:54,416 --> 01:27:55,474
[Thunder]

1114
01:27:55,550 --> 01:27:56,482
[Whispering]
Forever.

1115
01:27:58,019 --> 01:27:59,611
Oh, God.

1116
01:28:01,356 --> 01:28:02,345
Kell!

1117
01:28:04,225 --> 01:28:06,056
Jacob Kell!

1118
01:28:08,396 --> 01:28:10,296
Revenge...

1119
01:28:10,365 --> 01:28:13,562
will never bring you redemption,

1120
01:28:13,635 --> 01:28:16,297
so I'm going to do it for you.

1121
01:28:18,006 --> 01:28:19,064
Aah.

1122
01:28:21,509 --> 01:28:24,171
Is that all you've got?

1123
01:28:33,321 --> 01:28:34,652
(Kell)Dunc.

1124
01:28:34,723 --> 01:28:36,213
I'd thought
I'd be home for dinner...

1125
01:28:36,291 --> 01:28:38,759
an hour ago, but
this is very impressive.

1126
01:28:40,629 --> 01:28:41,994
Come on.

1127
01:28:42,063 --> 01:28:43,792
Come on.What are you
waiting for?

1128
01:28:43,865 --> 01:28:45,628
I'd be delighted.
Yaah!

1129
01:28:57,379 --> 01:28:59,210
Impressive...

1130
01:29:00,448 --> 01:29:01,506
isn't it?

1131
01:29:01,583 --> 01:29:03,073
Uhh!

1132
01:29:03,151 --> 01:29:04,140
Duncan!

1133
01:29:04,219 --> 01:29:05,277
[ Drops Sword ]

1134
01:29:09,591 --> 01:29:13,755
You see at last your fate!

1135
01:29:13,828 --> 01:29:15,489
Yes!

1136
01:29:15,563 --> 01:29:16,928
Because this game is done!

1137
01:29:22,637 --> 01:29:24,332
Uhh!

1138
01:29:25,607 --> 01:29:27,040
Well, look on the bright side.

1139
01:29:27,108 --> 01:29:29,838
At least
you went down swinging.

1140
01:29:29,911 --> 01:29:31,139
[Connor's Voice]
Jacob Kell.

1141
01:29:33,314 --> 01:29:35,441
(Connor)
Time for redemption.

1142
01:29:38,520 --> 01:29:41,182
The game isn't over yet.

1143
01:29:42,657 --> 01:29:43,749
(Connor)
What's the matter?

1144
01:29:43,825 --> 01:29:47,261
Don't you want to be inside me?

1145
01:29:50,098 --> 01:29:51,258
(Connor's Voice)
In the end-

1146
01:29:51,332 --> 01:29:54,199
[ Duncan's Voice]
...there can be only one.

1147
01:30:05,180 --> 01:30:06,875
[Connor's Voice]
And you're not it.

1148
01:30:06,948 --> 01:30:08,609
Uhh!

1149
01:30:08,683 --> 01:30:10,173
Call ya.

1150
01:30:31,806 --> 01:30:35,799
No!

1151
01:30:35,877 --> 01:30:37,845
[Screaming]

1152
01:30:40,615 --> 01:30:42,549
Aah!

1153
01:30:42,617 --> 01:30:44,608
[Screaming]

1154
01:31:18,920 --> 01:31:20,854
[Wind Blows]

1155
01:31:46,214 --> 01:31:49,149
Hope you found peace,
my friend.

1156
01:31:52,453 --> 01:31:56,822
Oh, Bonnie Portmore

1157
01:31:56,891 --> 01:32:01,487
I am sorry to see

1158
01:32:01,563 --> 01:32:06,466
Such a woeful destruction

1159
01:32:06,534 --> 01:32:11,369
Of your ornament tree

1160
01:32:11,439 --> 01:32:16,604
For it stood on your shore

1161
01:32:16,678 --> 01:32:20,978
For many's the long day

1162
01:32:21,049 --> 01:32:27,454
Till the long boats from Antrim

1163
01:32:27,522 --> 01:32:33,950
Came to float it away

1164
01:32:34,929 --> 01:32:36,487
[Wind Blowing]

1165
01:33:24,979 --> 01:33:27,140
So,why are you here?

1166
01:33:27,215 --> 01:33:29,445
You hoping you'd find me?

1167
01:33:32,153 --> 01:33:34,053
For whatever reason,
Kell made his choice.

1168
01:33:38,126 --> 01:33:40,754
So, um,

1169
01:33:40,828 --> 01:33:42,489
what now?

1170
01:33:45,333 --> 01:33:47,699
Trust.

1171
01:33:47,769 --> 01:33:50,203
You can always trust me, Faith.

1172
01:33:50,271 --> 01:33:52,603
Faith is dead.

1173
01:33:52,674 --> 01:33:56,007
I thought we'd give
Kate another chance.

1174
01:34:06,788 --> 01:34:09,621
Not yet.

1175
01:34:09,691 --> 01:34:11,454
(Faith, Whispering)
Till the day we are reborn.

1176
01:34:11,526 --> 01:34:14,188
You hold onto it for me.

1177
01:34:14,262 --> 01:34:16,127
We've got plenty of time.

